OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FAny baptised Catholic can be elected
OL,6,Fpope, but since 1379 every pope has
OL,7,Fbeen selected from the College of
OL,8,FCardinals - the group who cast the
OL,9,Fvotes at the conclave.
OL,11,FCardinals are senior members of the
OL,12,Fclergy, many who are bishops and
OL,13,Farchbishops appointed by the pope.
OL,15,FThe rules of the conclave, as of
OL,16,FJanuary 22, 2025, stated there are 138
OL,17,Felectors - and therefore 138 eligible
OL,18,Fpapal candidates - of the 252
OL,19,Fcardinals.
