OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FOnly those under the age of 80 may
OL,6,Ftake part in the secret ballot.
OL,8,FHow does the vote take place?
OL,10,FOnce the cardinals have arrived, the
OL,11,Fconclave begins with a special morning
OL,12,FMass in St Peter's Basilica. In the
OL,13,Fafternoon, the cardinals walk to the
OL,14,FSistine Chapel to start the voting
OL,15,Fprocess.
OL,17,FThe College of Cardinals then take a
OL,18,Fvow of secrecy inside the chapel and,
OL,19,Fwith the exception of a few workers,
OL,20,Fno one else is allowed in.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
