OL,3,CConclave: How is a new Pope elected?
OL,5,FThe names are then counted and if a
OL,6,Fname has received two-thirds of the
OL,7,Fvotes, the pope has been elected.
OL,9,FIf the first ballot does not produce a
OL,10,Fresult, a maximum of four ballots are
OL,11,Fheld on each successive day: two in
OL,12,Feach morning and two in each afternoon.
OL,14,FThe process is repeated for three
OL,15,Fdays, after which there is a day's
OL,16,Frest for prayer, reflection and
OL,17,Finformal discussions.
OL,19,FThe voting then begins again for a
OL,20,Fseries of seven more ballots and then
OL,21,Fanother break.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
